<Algorithm code="           1. Let _keys_ be a new empty List.           1. Let _str_ be _O_.[[StringData]].           1. Assert: _str_ is a String.           1. Let _len_ be the length of _str_.           1. For each integer _i_ such that 0 ≤ _i_ &lt; _len_, in ascending order, do             1. Append ! ToString(𝔽(_i_)) to _keys_.           1. For each own property key _P_ of _O_ such that _P_ is an array index and ! ToIntegerOrInfinity(_P_) ≥ _len_, in ascending numeric index order, do             1. Append _P_ to _keys_.           1. For each own property key _P_ of _O_ such that _P_ is a String and _P_ is not an array index, in ascending chronological order of property creation, do             1. Append _P_ to _keys_.           1. For each own property key _P_ of _O_ such that _P_ is a Symbol, in ascending chronological order of property creation, do             1. Append _P_ to _keys_.           1. Return _keys_.         ">
